13. DATA COLLECTION, CONNECTIVITY, AND PRIVACY NOTICE

Radio Player Pro is designed to play internet radio streams and may connect to
third-party services required for its functionality, including public station
directory services and third-party streaming endpoints selected by the user.

The Software may store local preferences and operational data on the user's
device, including favorites, last-played station information, cached station
metadata, volume and playback settings, logs, and temporary cache files.

Except as separately disclosed by BubblesTheDev, the Software is not intended to
send telemetry, analytics, or advertising identifiers to BubblesTheDev.
However, third-party radio directory services, content delivery networks, or
stream providers may receive network requests, IP address information, and other
technical connection data as part of normal application use.

Users are responsible for reviewing the privacy practices and terms of any
third-party station directories, streaming providers, or related services they
access through the Software.

